  "prompt": "What is human right?",
  "response": "Human rights are fundamental rights and freedoms that are inherent to all human beings, regardless of race, gender, nationality, ethnicity, language, religion, or any other status. They are designed to ensure human dignity, protect individuals from abuse, and promote fair and just treatment. Key characteristics of human rights include:\n\n1. Universal: They apply to everyone\n2. Inalienable: Cannot be taken away\n3. Indivisible: All rights are equally important\n\nSome fundamental human rights include:\n\n1. Right to life\n2. Right to liberty and security\n3. Freedom from torture\n4. Right to privacy\n5. Freedom of expression\n6. Right to education\n7. Right to work\n8. Right to health\n9. Freedom from discrimination\n10. Right to a fair trial\n\nThese rights are protected by various international documents, including:\n\n1. Universal Declaration of Human Rights (1948)\n2. International Covenant on Civil and Political Rights\n3. International Covenant on Economic, Social and Cultural Rights\n\nOrganizations like the United Nations and various human rights groups work to promote and protect these rights globally.\n\nHuman rights aim to ensure that all people are treated with respect, fairness, and equality, regardless of their background or circumstances.",
